node.text:
More than the launch of unparalleled works of jewelry craft, @Bulgari's Magnifica High Jewelry collection is a celebration of rebirth. Honored through magnificent muses, music, and Milan, take a look at Bvlgari's latest high jewelry collection.
 
Models: @vittoria, @lilyaldridge @heconghc, @solangesmith and @blesnyaminher
Special Guests: @andreabocelliofficial @beatricevenezi
Project by @oma.eu
Director @tommaso.ottomano
DOP@ mrcodepa
Stylist @sagliogeraldine
Music @guazzonemarco 
Production @studio.april
#Bvlgari #BvlgariJewelry #BvlgariHighJewelry #BvlgariMagnifica #Milan

node.text: After making her #NYFW modeling debut at @ProenzaSchouler, @EllaEmhoff landed a knitwear collaboration with Batsheva Hay (@batshevadress). The 21-year-old student, model, and designer met up with Hay amid NYFW—and #GoodMorningVogue was there to capture their conversations about materials, fit, and texture, plus Ella's rise to fame in the wake of the inauguration of President Joe Biden and Emhoff’s step-mother, Kamala Harris, in January.

node.text: This month, Vogue joined forces with an army of photographers and models all around the globe—stable Zoom connections required, please!—and sent the best and brightest of the new collections via courier services everywhere from Beijing to Brazil, Lagos to Los Angeles. Our concept? Simple, glorious movement: After a year of stasis, immobility and lockdowns, we wanted to see spring fashion breaking free. These are the looks we love, shot by the photographers we adore, on the run and out for a walk, a swim, a dance. Tap the link in our bio to see more.

node.text:
Today, @KamalaHarris became the first woman of color ever sworn in as vice president of the United States.

To celebrate this moment, twelve young women discussing what it means to them to see a Black woman of Indian descent elected to the second-highest office in the land. “Every little girl sees that this is a country of possibility,” @KamalaHarris states in one address, and that sentiment is widely echoed. “She reminds me every day that I am capable and worthy of my wildest dreams,” says one participant.

Director @rombokob
Producer @aliwebb_producer
Casting Director: Rebecca Dealy
Archival Research: Manon Blackman
Editor @ann_lupo
GFX @horatiobaltz
Color @carlosfloresfilms
Mix @cstropko
Post Production @forager.tv

node.title: 12 Girls on What Kamala Harris Becoming Vice President Means to Them

node.text: Throughout the political tumult of 2020, @janayathefuture was one of the most prominent voices to become a source of healing and hope. Reflecting on this week’s events, Khan points out the lack of police presence at the Capitol, a fact that exposes, in their own words, “a clear double standard for how Black protestors have been treated over the past several years. What we know to be true is that there is a way that white rage is celebrated in this country and Black grief is criminalized.” To hear more, make sure to check out Khan’s Sunday Sermons, returning tomorrow 1/10  at 12PM PST on their account.

node.title: @janayathefuture on Moving Forward from the Capitol Riots

node.text:
“I have a big young, queer contingent to my fan base, which is so divine to me,” @Lorde says. “You think you know what your kids will be like—you think they’ll just be like you, like, a million little yous. In the same way that if you wrote a book, maybe you’d imagine it would only be interesting to people like you. But it’s different.” 

“I have much cynicism,” she goes on, “but not about what I know to be the alchemical thing that happens in my work. The work is very powerful to people. My fans are young, and I just know that they look to me for a lot emotionally and spiritually. But it’s an attachment like any other. You want it to be a healthy one. It needs to be right for both of us, and there needs to be that understanding that mummy does go away to the other room, and she will come back!”

Lorde opens up about her special fanbase in our October profile at the link in our bio. Photographed by @theodegueltzl, styled by #CamillaNickerson, written by @RobertJHaskell, Vogue, October 2021.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Vogue on September 08, 2021 tagging @farahomidi, @lorde, and @jimmypaulhair. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
“I totally agree and disagree with [@Lorde] that she’s not suited for celebrity,” says the pop star's close friend, photographer Ophelia Mikkelson Jones (@opheliaafm), who shot the cover art for Solar Power during a road trip along the New Zealand coast.

“She’s a shy and reserved woman, but she has this incredible intelligence. She’s so alert, always awake and watching, and she has the most insane memory. I’m stoked by the idea that someone in her position would have these qualities, and they also make her a great friend...She is just someone who will look you in the eye and be completely present.”

Tap the link in our bio to read the full October profile, starring @Lorde. Photographed by @theodegueltzl, styled by #CamillaNickerson, written by @RobertJHaskell, Vogue, October 2021.

node.text:
“I’m great at my job, but I’m not sure I’m the man for the job,” Ella lla Marija Lani Yelich-O’Connor, who makes music under the name @Lorde, explains. “I’m a highly sensitive person. I’m not built for pop star life. To have a public-facing existence is something I find really intense and is something I’m not good at. That natural charisma is not what I have. I have the brain in the jar.” 

In conversation, Yelich-O’Connor does not refer to herself as a pop star frequently. Ever since the song “Royals” brought her into the spotlight at the age of 16, Yelich-O’Connor has politely insisted on a sparingly dosed celebrity. “But for whatever reason people have allowed me to say, Okay, I’m going to come and do the thing—do the shoot, do the red carpet, speak to the journalists, put the music out—and when I’ve done it to the point of total exhaustion, when I have completely quenched that thirst, I’m going to go home, and you’re not going to see me for two or three or four years."

At the link in our bio, @Lorde opens up about her blissed-out comeback into the scene with her new album, #SolarPower. Read the full October profile there. Photographed by @theodegueltzl, styled by #CamillaNickerson, written by @RobertJHaskell, Vogue, October 2021.

node.text: #NewYorkFashionWeek skipped right back into action after an 18-month pause with Collina Strada’s spring 2022 show. Situated on Brooklyn Grange’s rooftop garden in Sunset Park, the show was a raucous welcome back to business as usual—although there is almost nothing usual about the way designer Hillary Taymour does business. Tap the link in our bio to see every look, and to read our full review. Photographed by @hunterabrams

node.text: Congratulations are in order for @kyliejenner and @travisscott! The couple has officially announced they are expecting their second child together—in an exceptionally adorable way, we might add. Tap the link in our bio for more. #regram @kyliejenner

node.text: @lilyjcollins is officially married! The actor just shared pictures from her Colorado wedding to director Charlie McDowell, for which she wore a long-sleeved, hooded lace gown by @RalphLauren. It’s one of the few wedding dresses the brand has designed! Tap the link in our bio for all the details. Photo: @cedarandpines
